Here's how to find us. Find a specific program and when it airs. See what's airing on WETA's 5 channels. Learn more about WETA's broadcast area and get tips on how to set up your antenna. Download the PBS Video App on your device and gain access to your favorite PBS and local shows. Watch on your schedule, anytime, anywhere! From history to art, music to cuisine, WETA produces a wide variety of shows which explore the people, places and culture of our region. WETA Arts celebrates visual and performing art in Greater Washington, presenting a variety of stories, profiles, and discussions which highlight emerging and established artists alike. WETA's newest series discovers and reveals the standout dishes at a wide array of the region’s best restaurants, from the latest dining hot spots to strip-mall eateries serving up authentic global cuisines. Join the mother-daughter duo Laurita and Lauren Portee on road trips to amazing destinations near the nation’s capital. WETA's house-hunting series spotlights a wide array of neighborhoods and properties throughout the national capital area while celebrating each area’s history, culture, notable places and flavor. Discover the variety of programs WETA produces especially for Washington area audiences. In addition to your favorite Masterpiece series on our flagship channel, our WETA UK channel presents the best in contemporary and classic British programming, 24 hours a day, 7 days a week! This Australian drama follows two sisters who are reunited following the death of their father. When they jointly inherit the cash-strapped family ranch, city slicker Tess (Bridie Carter, 800 Words) and farm girl Claire (Lisa Chappell) work to save the property and rebuild their relationship. Judi Dench and Geoffrey Palmer star in this beloved British romantic comedy about two former lovers whose lives intersect again 40 years after they lost touch with each other. Based on the crime-novel series by author Caroline Graham, Midsomer Murders follows the efforts of Detective Chief Inspector John Barnaby to solve crimes that occur in the wealthy, isolated English county of Midsomer. A website by Anglophiles, for Anglophiles! Read about your favorite shows, and don't forget to tune into Telly Visions: The Podcast! See what's on WETA UK now! Visit the WETA UK shop for all your Anglophile needs and help support WETA programming!
